Package ca.corefacility.gview.map.gui.editor.node

Provides for different nodes of the Style Editor tree.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Slotable
    This interface is intended to allow tree nodes that represent 'styles' that can be placed in slots to interface appropriately.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BackboneNode
    The node class for the backbone panel.
    BackboneSlotNode
    The node used to represent the backbone as it sits in GView's collection of slots.
    FeatureContainerNode
    This node class is an abstract representation of nodes that are intended to represent styles that contain features, such as slots and sets.
    GlobalNode
    The node class for the global style.
    LabelNode
    The node class for the label styles.
    LegendItemNode
    The node class for the legend item styles.
    LegendNode
    The node class for the legend.
    LegendStyleNode
    The node class for the legend style.
    NodeBuilder
    This class is responsible for building nodes for the style editor tree object.
    PlotNode
    The node class for the plot styles.
    PropertyMapperNode
    The node class for the property mapper panel.
    RootNode
    The root node.
    RulerNode
    The node class for the ruler style.
    SetNode
    The node class for the set styles.
    SlotNode
    The node class for the slot styles.
    SlotsNode
    The node class for the slots.
    StyleEditorNode
    The default node class.
    TooltipNode
    The node class for the tool tip styles.
